intake.trainingGoal: Build raw strength, increase powerlifting total, maintain athleticism
intake.additionalInfo: Former D1 college football linebacker. Played 4 years, graduated 2014. Got away from serious lifting for a few years - desk job, life happened. Ready to get back to being strong. Joined a powerlifting-focused gym with competition equipment. Running 5/3/1 because it's proven and I know how to grind. Goal: hit my old college numbers - 405 squat, 315 bench, 495 deadlift, 205 OHP. Currently rebuilding that base.

programs.name: 5/3/1 Strength Builder
programs.description: Jim Wendler's 5/3/1 program for building raw strength. 4-day split with each day focused on one main lift (Squat, Bench, Deadlift, OHP). Progressive overload through calculated percentages with First Set Last (FSL) for additional volume.

workoutPlan.phaseExplanation: Classic 5/3/1 programming with 3-week waves: Week 1 (5s), Week 2 (3s), Week 3 (5/3/1). Deload every 4th week. Each day focuses on one main lift with assistance work.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 1 Day 1. First day of 5/3/1. Felt good to be back under a heavy bar. Squat groove coming back.

exerciseLogs.notes: 5/5/5+ week. Hit 8 on AMRAP. Depth felt good, knees tracking. Getting my groove back.
FSL 5x5. Legs are remembering what to do.
Good hamstring stretch. Posterior chain waking up.
Core is weak. Need to build this back up.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 1 Bench Day. Upper body strength still there. Muscle memory is real.

exerciseLogs.notes: 5/5/5+ week. Bar path felt natural. Chest remembered the movement.
FSL 5x5. Nice pump.
Back is still solid. Years of football rows paying off.
Bodyweight feels light at 225. Good sign.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 1 Deadlift Day. This is where I shine. Pulling has always been my strongest lift.

exerciseLogs.notes: 5/5/5+ week. 310x9 felt EASY. Lockout was strong. This is where I live.
FSL. Grip held fine. Chalk is my friend.
Thoracic mobility needs work. Core stayed tight though.
Traps are still there. Football shrug strength.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 1 OHP Day. Overhead has always been my weakest. Time to build it up.

exerciseLogs.notes: 5/5/5+ week. Only hit 6 on AMRAP. OHP always humbles me.
FSL. Kept it strict - no leg drive.
225 lbs moving through pull-ups. Not bad for a big man.
Arms day is leg day for your arms - football coach wisdom.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 2 Squat Day. 3s week. Body is adapting. Less DOMS than last week.

exerciseLogs.notes: 3/3/3+ week. 285x7! Felt explosive out of the hole. Legs are coming back.
FSL 5x5. Speed was good.
Pushing the volume. Quads are responding.
Core getting stronger. Hit all reps this time.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 2 Bench Day. 3s week. Answered week 2 check-in: going great! This program is working.

exerciseLogs.notes: 3/3/3+ week. 220x6! Bar speed was smooth. Touch and go, no pause.
FSL. Technique dialed in.
Added 25 lb plate. Bodyweight was too easy.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 2 Deadlift Day. 3s week. Heavy pulls are my happy place.

exerciseLogs.notes: 3/3/3+ week. 330x8! Felt like I had more in the tank. Speed off the floor was explosive.
FSL. Focused on hip hinge pattern.
Mobility improving. Elbows staying up better.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 2 OHP Day. 3s week. Still my weakest lift but grinding through.

exerciseLogs.notes: 3/3/3+ week. 140x5. Grinded the last rep. OHP is a mental battle.

workoutLogs.notes: Week 3 Squat Day. 5/3/1 week - the heavy week. Time to see what I've got.

checkIns.notes: Starting 5/3/1 program. Been away from serious lifting for a few years since college football. Ready to rebuild. Current 1RM estimates: Squat 335, Bench 245, Deadlift 365, OHP 165. Goal is to hit my old college numbers over this 16-week block.
End of cycle 1. Lifts moving well. Squat hit 295x7 on 1+ week, bench 220x6, deadlift 330x5, OHP 145x7. Body remembering the movement patterns. Football strength coming back. Up 2 lbs - good weight.
End of cycle 2. PRs on all lifts. Squat 320x5, bench 240x5, deadlift 360x4, OHP 160x5. Feeling like an athlete again. Deload felt necessary - volume catching up. Ready for the push in cycle 3.
End of cycle 3, workout 45. Hit all my major goals - Squat 365x3, Bench 275x2, Deadlift 405x1. Just need OHP. 90% through program. Taking the final deload then testing 1RMs. Former athlete is back.
